  }, "All structure would be fabricated from 15 series 8020."))), mdx("p", null, "\"2\", \"5\", and \"7\" combine to set the end of the passenger side galley.  Specifically, we locate the sink width-wise with the faucet/sprayer adjacent and forward in order to minimize depth to satisfy \"2\" and provide the shower function of \"5\".  We add structure on either side as this section will contain heavy stuff per \"6\".  We note this structure has to sit forward of the C-Pillar bump out to satisfy \"2\" and \"5\".  We add some margin to make sure our counter, with holes for the sink and faucet, has decent ligament. "), mdx("p", null, "All this yields a slider opening of 29\" meaning we can satisfy \"4\" with margin.  The resulting cabinet also has room for the three jerry cans (19.5\") inside satisfying \"6\".  We ultimately consumed some of the margin to allow us to tuck the water pump forward of the sink directly under the counter top to maximize useful space in this cabinet."), mdx("p", null, "Adding more constraints/requirements:"), mdx("ol", {
